We conducted the study during June 2010-March 2012 in Senegal's rural Sine-Saloum area, a dry sahelian ecosystem with 2 typical seasons: dry (November-May) and rainy (June-October). We obtained written consent for every person included in the study. The National Ethics Committee of Senegal approved the study. (8) . In parallel, we collected blood samples from a control group of 385 healthy, afebrile villagers; 62.5% of these study participants were <15 years of age, and the sex ratio was 1:1. 


